  "summary": "Tyson Hardin, a right-handed pitcher, was a 12th-round pick in 2024 who successfully transitioned from a college reliever to a professional starter in 2025. He earned the Brewers' Minor League Pitcher of the Year award, impressing with strong control and a refined five-pitch mix including a 92-95 mph fastball and an above-average sweeping slider. He reached Double-A in 2025 and is projected to provide rotation depth for the Brewers in the near future.",
